          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">32 F</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Palmyra</placeName>, <date>Sept.
                                                  18<hi rend="sup">th</hi>, 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p>Dear friend:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have written this article more than a month<lb/>
                                        ago for you. An eye infection however prevented me to
                                        finish<lb/> it sooner and copy it for you. At the moment I
                                        am vacationing<lb/> and hasten to send it to you. I do not
                                        doubt that you will have<lb/> to correct it. Very much so
                                        indeed. (But I am sure that this<lb/> article will then be
                                        not unworthy of your journal and may be a<lb/> seed grain
                                        for many a good decision.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I presume that you have received by now the
                                        bible<lb/> and one sheet of <persName>Reggio's</persName>
                                        DENKBUCHLEIN. You would make me happy<lb/> and honor him who
                                        deserves honor if you would print in one of<lb/> your
                                        journals a literary biographic note concerning this
                                        great<lb/> old man, with ever young spirit. I also sent you
                                        two journals<lb/> (I don't have any more. I believe many
                                        more are in existence.)<lb/> of a talmudic dictionary. I
                                        don't have any use for it. Maybe<lb/> you care to have this
                                        work sent to you from <placeName>Europe</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Sometime ago I asked you to design statutes
                                        (STATUTEN<lb/> ENTWURF). The congregation for which I did
                                        that is a small one and<lb/> poor one with a
                                                  <sic>Bohemean</sic> rite (similar to the small
                                        Polish rite).<lb/> This congregation now made some statutes
                                        for itself, will try them<lb/> out for a while and after
                                        they have experience will draw them up<lb/> anew with the
                                        aid of sample statutes and shape them properly.<lb/> (28
                                        members, $7.50 for seats for men and wife; 5. for
                                        single<lb/> persons; 10Â¢ weekly contribution.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Well, good-bye dear friend, and allow the old
                                        wish,<lb/> *KETIBA wa-ha-ti-ma tobah.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Most cordially yours,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>*<sic>Iscribed</sic> for good life.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Addressed: <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>,
                                        Editor Occident, etc. <placeName>Philada</placeName>.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Palmyra</placeName>
                                        <date>Sept. 18, 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p>Translation in General files.</p>
                              <p>Letter speaks of a manuscript sent <persName>Leeser</persName>, for
                                        publication<lb/> It also speaks of having sent
                                                  <sic>abible</sic> and one sheet of
                                                  <persName>Reggio's</persName><lb/> Denkbuchlein.
                                        Mentions other books which <persName>Leeser</persName> may
                                        want.</p>
